        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 4:55PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
across northern Crockett County, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
